---
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <!-- META / SEO -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Selected Work | Leapintel Solutions</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Representative examples of how complex technology leadership challenges have been addressed across public sector, healthcare, and enterprise environments."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/favicon.ico" />

    <meta property="og:title" content="Selected Work | Leapintel Solutions" />
    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="How leadership, structure, and execution have been brought into alignment across complex environments."
    />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://leapintel.com/selected-work" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://leapintel.com/chicago-skyline.jpg" />

    <style>
      /* =================================
         ROOT VARIABLES
         ================================= */
      :root {
        --navy: #142033;
        --white: #ffffff;
        --max-width: 1200px;
      }

      /* =================================
         BASE / RESET
         ================================= */
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      html,
      body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
        background: #ffffff;
        color: #1f2937;
      }

      body {
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      img {
        display: block;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      /* =================================
         SHARED SECTION STYLES
         ================================= */
      .section-container {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 24px;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 0 0 22px;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 2.6rem);
        font-weight: 500;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      }

      .section-intro {
        max-width: 54ch;
        margin-bottom: 44px;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      /* =================================
         HEADER / NAVIGATION
         ================================= */
      .site-header {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 20;
        width: 100%;
        background: #dbe3ec;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.08);
      }

      .nav-shell {
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 22px 24px;
      }

      .nav-bar {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 24px;
        position: relative;
      }

      .brand {
        white-space: nowrap;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: 1.18rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 32px;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        font-weight: 500;
      }

      .nav-links a {
        transition: color 0.2s ease, opacity 0.2s ease;
      }

      .nav-links a:hover {
        color: #172132;
        opacity: 1;
      }

      .nav-toggle {
        display: none;
        width: 44px;
        height: 44px;
        padding: 0;
        border: none;
        background: transparent;
        cursor: pointer;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 5px;
      }

      .nav-toggle span {
        display: block;
        width: 22px;
        height: 2px;
        background: #172132;
        border-radius: 999px;
        transition: transform 0.2s ease, opacity 0.2s ease;
      }

      /* =================================
         BUTTONS
         ================================= */
      .button-primary,
      .button-secondary {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        height: 46px;
        padding: 0 20px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1;
        text-decoration: none;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        appearance: none;
        -webkit-appearance: none;
        transition:
          transform 0.2s ease,
          background 0.2s ease,
          border-color 0.2s ease,
          color 0.2s ease,
          box-shadow 0.2s ease;
      }

      .button-primary {
        color: #172132;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
        box-shadow: none;
      }

      .button-primary:hover {
        transform: translateY(-1px);
        background: #faf6f6;
      }

      .button-secondary {
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.98);
        background: rgba(10, 20, 35, 0.34);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.34);
        box-shadow: none;
        backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
        -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
      }

      .button-secondary:hover {
        background: rgba(10, 20, 35, 0.44);
        border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.42);
      }

      /* =================================
         SELECTED WORK PAGE HEADER
         ================================= */
      .selected-header {
        padding: 80px 0;
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #eef2f7 0%, #f7f9fc 100%);
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.06);
      }

      .selected-header-inner {
        max-width: 940px;
      }

      .selected-eyebrow {
        margin: 0 0 14px;
        color: #5b6777;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .selected-title {
        margin: 0 0 22px;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 4vw, 3.8rem);
        font-weight: 500;
        line-height: 1.08;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        max-width: 20ch;
        transform: translateX(-2px);
      }

      .selected-lead {
        max-width: 60ch;
        margin: 0;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 1.18rem;
        line-height: 1.72;
      }

      .selected-hero-support {
        max-width: 62ch;
        margin: 28px 0 0;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      /* =================================
         SELECTED WORK SECTIONS
         ================================= */
      .selected-work {
        padding: 90px 0 95px;
        background: #ffffff;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.05);
      }

      .selected-work-alt {
        background: #f6f8fb;
      }

      .selected-work-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.92fr) minmax(0, 1.28fr);
        gap: 40px 64px;
        align-items: start;
      }

      /* LEFT COLUMN */
      .selected-work-left h2 {
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        max-width: 20ch;
      }

      .selected-descriptor {
        margin: 0 0 22px;
        color: #5b6777;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1.65;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      }

      .selected-bullet-intro {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        line-height: 1.5;
        letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      }

      .selected-list {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        list-style: none;
      }

      .selected-list li {
        position: relative;
        margin: 0 0 12px;
        padding-left: 18px;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 0.98rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      .selected-list li:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .selected-list li::before {
        content: "";
        position: absolute;
        top: 0.72em;
        left: 0;
        width: 6px;
        height: 6px;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.34);
        transform: translateY(-50%);
      }

      /* RIGHT COLUMN */
      .selected-work-right {
        max-width: 62ch;
        padding-top: 98px;
      }

      .selected-copy-block {
        margin-bottom: 28px;
      }

      .selected-copy-block:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
      }

      .selected-copy-label {
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: 0.82rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .selected-copy-block p {
        margin: 0;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }

      /* =================================
         CROSS-ENVIRONMENT THEMES
         ================================= */
      .selected-themes {
        padding: 95px 0 100px;
        background: #f6f8fb;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.05);
        
      }

      .selected-themes-intro {
        max-width: 108ch;
      }

      .selected-themes-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        gap: 28px;
      }

      .theme-card {
        padding: 28px 24px;
        background: #ffffff;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.05);
        border-radius: 16px;
        box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.035);
      }

      .theme-card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 12px;
        color: #172132;
        font-size: 1.04rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .theme-card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: #4b5563;
        font-size: 0.96rem;
        line-height: 1.72;
      }

      /* =================================
         SELECTED WORK CTA
         ================================= */
      .selected-cta {
        padding: 100px 0 110px;
        background: var(--navy);
        text-align: center;
      }

      .selected-cta-inner {
        max-width: 760px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .selected-cta h2 {
        margin: 0 0 20px;
        color: #ffffff;
      }

      .selected-cta p {
        max-width: 56ch;
        margin: 0 auto 36px;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.82);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      /* =================================
         FOOTER
         ================================= */
      .site-footer {
        padding: 60px 24px 30px;
        color: #1f2937;
        background: #ffffff;
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.08);
      }

      .footer-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr 1fr;
        align-items: flex-start;
        gap: 28px;
        max-width: var(--max-width);
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      .footer-left {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 10px;
        margin-top: 4px;
      }

      .footer-logo {
        width: 130px;
        margin-bottom: 12px;
      }

      .footer-links {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 8px;
      }

      .footer-links a {
        color: #374151;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.4;
      }

      .footer-links a:hover {
        color: #111827;
      }

      .footer-contact p {
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .footer-contact a {
        color: #374151;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      .footer-bottom {
        margin-top: 40px;
        color: #6b7280;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        text-align: center;
      }

      /* =================================
         RESPONSIVE BREAKPOINTS
         ================================= */
      @media (max-width: 900px) {
        .nav-links {
          gap: 18px;
          font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .footer-container {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
          gap: 30px;
        }

        .selected-work-grid,
        .selected-themes-grid {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }

        .selected-header {
          padding: 140px 0 70px;
        }

        .selected-title {
          max-width: 16ch;
        }

        .selected-work-right {
          padding-top: 0;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 720px) {
        .nav-shell {
          padding: 18px;
        }

        .nav-bar {
          gap: 16px;
        }

        .brand {
          font-size: 1.05rem;
        }

        .nav-toggle {
          display: inline-flex;
        }

        .nav-links {
          display: none;
          position: absolute;
          top: calc(100% + 12px);
          left: 0;
          right: 0;
          z-index: 30;
          flex-direction: column;
          align-items: flex-start;
          gap: 0;
          padding: 10px 0;
          background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.98);
          border: 1px solid rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.08);
          border-radius: 14px;
          box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(23, 33, 50, 0.08);
        }

        .nav-links.is-open {
          display: flex;
        }

        .nav-links a {
          width: 100%;
          padding: 12px 16px;
          font-size: 0.92rem;
          line-height: 1.3;
        }

        .nav-links a:hover {
          background: rgba(219, 227, 236, 0.45);
        }

        .button-primary,
        .button-secondary {
          width: 100%;
          min-height: 46px;
          font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .selected-header {
          padding: 72px 0 56px;
        }

        .selected-title {
          margin: 0 0 18px;
          font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 8vw, 3.2rem);
          line-height: 1.05;
          max-width: 100%;
        }

        .selected-lead {
          font-size: 1.05rem;
          line-height: 1.65;
        }

        .selected-work,
        .selected-themes,
        .selected-cta {
          padding-top: 72px;
          padding-bottom: 76px;
        }

        .theme-card {
          padding: 24px 20px;
        }

        .selected-copy-block {
          margin-bottom: 24px;
        }
      }

      @media (max-width: 520px) {
        .brand {
          font-size: 1.02rem;
        }

        .selected-header-inner {
          max-width: 100%;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <!-- SITE HEADER -->
    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="nav-shell">
        <div class="nav-bar">
          <a class="brand" href="/">Leapintel Solutions</a>

          <button
            class="nav-toggle"
            type="button"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-controls="primary-navigation"
            aria-label="Open navigation"
          >
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
          </button>

          <nav class="nav-links" id="primary-navigation" aria-label="Primary">
            <a href="/about">About</a>
            <a href="/engagement">Engagement Models</a>
            <a href="/focus-areas">Focus Areas</a>
            <a href="/selected-work">Selected Work</a>
            <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <!-- SELECTED WORK PAGE HEADER -->
      <section class="selected-header">
        <div class="section-container">
          <div class="selected-header-inner">
            <p class="selected-eyebrow">Selected Work</p>

            <h1 class="selected-title">
              How these challenges have been addressed across complex environments and organizational contexts.
            </h1>

            <p class="selected-lead">
              The work has spanned public sector, healthcare, enterprise modernization,
              and large-scale transformation environments. While each context differs,
              the underlying challenges are often consistent.
            </p>

            <p class="selected-hero-support">
              The examples below are not presented as a comprehensive history.
              They are representative situations that reflect how leadership,
              structure, and execution have been brought into alignment across
              different settings.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SELECTED WORK 01 -->
      <section class="selected-work">
        <div class="section-container">
          <div class="selected-work-grid">
            <!-- LEFT COLUMN: TITLE / DESCRIPTOR / CONTEXT BULLETS -->
            <div class="selected-work-left">
              <h2>Leadership Continuity &amp; Transition</h2>

              <p class="selected-descriptor">
                Maintaining direction and decision clarity during periods of leadership change.
              </p>

              <p class="selected-bullet-intro">Representative contexts:</p>

              <ul class="selected-list">
                <li>executive departures or vacancies that create uncertainty</li>
                <li>organizations continuing to operate without strong directional alignment</li>
                <li>transitions where decision-making slows as authority becomes less clear</li>
                <li>environments that need continuity before long-term leadership is established</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: CONTEXT / APPROACH / REPRESENTATIVE ENVIRONMENTS -->
            <div class="selected-work-right">
              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Context</p>
                <p>
                  Leadership transitions often introduce more disruption than expected.
                  Even when operations continue, decision-making can slow, priorities can
                  become less defined, and accountability can begin to diffuse.
                  Organizations may keep moving, but without clear direction or consistent alignment.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Approach</p>
                <p>
                  Work in these situations has focused on preserving continuity while
                  preparing the organization for its next phase of leadership.
                  This includes maintaining decision cadence, clarifying authority,
                  stabilizing priorities, and ensuring that initiatives continue to move
                  forward without unnecessary disruption. Just as importantly, the goal
                  is to leave behind structure, clarity, and forward movement rather than unresolved issues.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Representative Environments</p>
                <p>
                  This work has included government agencies, enterprise organizations,
                  and settings undergoing leadership transition, restructuring, or executive change.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SELECTED WORK 02 -->
      <section class="selected-work selected-work-alt">
        <div class="section-container">
          <div class="selected-work-grid">
            <!-- LEFT COLUMN: TITLE / DESCRIPTOR / CONTEXT BULLETS -->
            <div class="selected-work-left">
              <h2>Stabilization &amp; Execution Recovery</h2>

              <p class="selected-descriptor">
                Restoring execution clarity where delivery has slowed or fragmented.
              </p>

              <p class="selected-bullet-intro">Representative contexts:</p>

              <ul class="selected-list">
                <li>active initiatives that no longer move with coherence</li>
                <li>too many priorities competing without real sequencing</li>
                <li>mixed signals around status, ownership, and risk</li>
                <li>leadership uncertainty about what is actually on track</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: CONTEXT / APPROACH / REPRESENTATIVE ENVIRONMENTS -->
            <div class="selected-work-right">
              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Context</p>
                <p>
                  In multiple environments, initiatives were active but lacked coherence.
                  Teams were working, priorities were shifting, and progress was difficult
                  to interpret. Leadership often received mixed signals about status, risk,
                  and ownership, making it difficult to determine where intervention was needed.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Approach</p>
                <p>
                  Work in these situations has focused on restoring execution clarity.
                  This includes re-establishing priorities, identifying where initiatives
                  are truly stalled, clarifying ownership, and reducing operational noise.
                  Governance structures are adjusted to improve decision flow, and reporting
                  is refined to better reflect actual progress and risk. The objective is
                  to restore confidence in execution and create a more reliable path forward.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Representative Environments</p>
                <p>
                  This work has included large-scale enterprise settings and public sector
                  initiatives, including healthcare environments, state-level programs,
                  and multi-team modernization efforts.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SELECTED WORK 03 -->
      <section class="selected-work">
        <div class="section-container">
          <div class="selected-work-grid">
            <!-- LEFT COLUMN: TITLE / DESCRIPTOR / CONTEXT BULLETS -->
            <div class="selected-work-left">
              <h2>Modernization Without Disruption</h2>

              <p class="selected-descriptor">
                Advancing modernization while maintaining operational continuity.
              </p>

              <p class="selected-bullet-intro">Representative contexts:</p>

              <ul class="selected-list">
                <li>legacy environments that cannot be left untouched</li>
                <li>modernization efforts that risk outrunning internal capacity</li>
                <li>organizations balancing improvement against continuity of service</li>
                <li>deeply embedded systems that support daily operations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: CONTEXT / APPROACH / REPRESENTATIVE ENVIRONMENTS -->
            <div class="selected-work-right">
              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Context</p>
                <p>
                  Modernization efforts often introduce risk when they are pursued without
                  sufficient alignment to operational realities. Legacy systems may need to
                  be replaced, restructured, or integrated, but core services must continue
                  without interruption. When modernization moves faster than organizational
                  readiness, it can create instability rather than improvement.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Approach</p>
                <p>
                  Work in these situations has focused on sequencing change in a way that
                  protects operations while still enabling progress. This includes aligning
                  stakeholders around practical tradeoffs, defining realistic transition paths,
                  and ensuring that modernization efforts remain grounded in execution capacity.
                  The goal is to introduce change in a way that is sustainable, controlled,
                  and aligned with how the organization actually operates.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Representative Environments</p>
                <p>
                  This work has included enterprise modernization efforts, healthcare systems,
                  and public sector settings where operational continuity and system reliability are critical.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SELECTED WORK 04 -->
      <section class="selected-work selected-work-alt">
        <div class="section-container">
          <div class="selected-work-grid">
            <!-- LEFT COLUMN: TITLE / DESCRIPTOR / CONTEXT BULLETS -->
            <div class="selected-work-left">
              <h2>Governance, Prioritization &amp; Operating Clarity</h2>

              <p class="selected-descriptor">
                Establishing the structures that keep decisions, priorities, and execution aligned.
              </p>

              <p class="selected-bullet-intro">Representative contexts:</p>

              <ul class="selected-list">
                <li>inconsistent decision-making across leaders or teams</li>
                <li>priorities shifting without a clear basis</li>
                <li>unclear ownership across cross-functional initiatives</li>
                <li>growing complexity without sufficient operating discipline</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- RIGHT COLUMN: CONTEXT / APPROACH / REPRESENTATIVE ENVIRONMENTS -->
            <div class="selected-work-right">
              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Context</p>
                <p>
                  In many organizations, challenges that appear technical are rooted in
                  governance and operating structure. Decision-making may be inconsistent,
                  priorities may shift without clear rationale, and teams may be asked to
                  execute without shared context or defined ownership. As complexity increases,
                  the absence of clear governance creates friction, slows execution, and reduces confidence in outcomes.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Approach</p>
                <p>
                  Work in these situations has focused on creating clarity in how decisions
                  are made and how work is prioritized. This includes defining governance
                  structures, establishing clearer decision rights, improving portfolio visibility,
                  and creating a more consistent rhythm for reviewing progress and risk.
                  The objective is to reduce ambiguity and create an operating environment
                  where execution becomes more predictable, visible, and aligned.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="selected-copy-block">
                <p class="selected-copy-label">Representative Environments</p>
                <p>
                  This work has included large-scale enterprise settings, cross-functional organizations,
                  and public sector systems where coordination across multiple stakeholders is required.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SELECTED WORK 05 -->
      <section class="selected-work">
        <div class="section-container">
