                <p>
                  Over time, technology organizations can become active without remaining aligned.
                  Initiatives expand, priorities compete, and teams respond to immediate demands,
                  but the broader direction becomes less clear. Leadership may begin to question
                  whether effort is translating into meaningful organizational impact.
